            <h1>7. Don't Repot Your Plants by Pulling Them!</h1>
            <p>Pulling a plant out will not only ruin the stems, leaves, and blossoms but will also tear roots. Damaged roots need to heal before they can fully take in nutrients, so pulling your plant out of its pot is never a good plan.<span id="dots">...</span><span id="more"></span> Check out our guide on repotting a plant to guarantee no damage to your plant.</p>
