            <h1>9. Always keep temperatures stable</h1>
            <p>keep your plant's home environment as stable as possible.<span id="dots">...</span><span id="more"></span> Extreme changes can stress plants out. Keep the temperature between 65 and 85 degrees F, and avoid placing your plants near radiators, A/C units, and forced-air vents, which can create hot or cold drafts.</p>
