            <h1>10. Cut the dead stuff.</h1>
            <p>To keep leaves growing, The Flower Shop Network says you must trim dead ends. <span id="dots">...</span><span id="more"></span>The process of pruning using scissors, pruning shears, or your hands can even be therapeutic. Bid goodbye to anything that's brown or spotted. A layer of dust on forgotten leaves blocks out sunlight, so regularly spritz plants with water and wipe down with a dry cloth.</p>
